# ==============================================================================
# NOTICE: RabbitMQ Credentials Configuration
# ==============================================================================
# In this specific drn-rabbit setup, setting RABBITMQ_DEFAULT_USER or 
# RABBITMQ_DEFAULT_PASS in this file will have NO EFFECT.
#
# Why?
# The custom rabbitmq-drn image uses `load_definitions = /etc/rabbitmq/definitions.json`.
# This instructs RabbitMQ to provision users, vhosts, and permissions directly 
# from the `image/definitions.json` file.
#
# How to change the password:
# The `drn` user and its password are hardcoded as a PBKDF2-SHA256 hash inside 
# `image/definitions.json`. To change the password, you must generate a new 
# hash and update it directly in that JSON file.
# ==============================================================================
